45. sed
	-> 
Command: sed
	[] sed 's/old/new/' file.txt -> Replace first match per line
	[] sed 's/old/new/g' file.txt -> Replace all matches per line (global)
	[] sed 's/old/new/2' file.txt -> Replace only the 2nd match per line
	[] sed 's/old/new/gi' file.txt -> Case-insensitive, all matches
	[] sed -i 's/old/new/g' file.txt -> Edit file in place
	[] sed -i.bak 's/old/new/g' file.txt -> Edit in place, keep backup as file.txt.bak
	[] sed -n '5p' file.txt -> Print only line 5
	[] sed -n '5,10p' file.txt -> Print lines 5–10
	[] sed '5d' file.txt -> Delete line 5
	[] sed '/pattern/d' file.txt -> Delete lines matching pattern
	[] sed '3i\text to insert' file.txt -> Insert before line 3
	[] sed '3a\text to append' file.txt -> Append after line 3

